SEC. 2. The ceramics processing plant shall have the following functions:

Study the efficient utilization of ceramic raw materials of the locality;

Process and compound whatever clay or other ceramics raw materials that may be found in the locality for sale at cost to potters;

Mix ceramics materials for glaze to be sold at cost to potters;

Construct a community kiln for the use of local potters at nominal cost;

Teach, guide and demonstrate to local potters the making of different kinds of ceramics products such as structural hollow clay blocks, building bricks, tiles, and household potter ware, like flower vases, art ware, containers, dinner ware, drinking vessels, insulators, etc; and

Conduct such researches or studies as may be necessary for the efficient and effective functioning of the plant.
